          int writePointer
          Single index for writing i.e. offset in file; grows from 0 to MAXINT. Invariants: writePointer<=readPointer[i]<=writePointer+bufferMaxSize for any i.

        • readPointer

          int[] readPointer
          Array of indexes, i.e. offsets in the file. They grow from 0 to MAXINT. Each points to the active (valid) location, unless it is equal to writePointer.

    • Class it.cnr.isti.thematrix.scripting.modules.BufferModule extends MatrixModule implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • numReaders

          int numReaders

        • Wpointer

          int Wpointer
          Single index for writing in to the buffer; points to a free location in the buffer; grow from 0 to MAXINT, it is wrapped around at the buffer bufferSize when accessing the data. Invariants: Wpointer<=Rpointer[i]<=Wpointer+bufferMaxSize for any i.

        • Rpointer

          int[] Rpointer
          Array of indexes, of bufferSize numReaders. They grow from 0 to MAXINT, wrapping around at the bufferSize of the buffer. Each points to the active (valid) location, unless it is equal to Wpointer.

        • leastRpointer

          int leastRpointer
